# Manual Sync on User-Facing Changes

Apply this rule whenever a change affects what end users see or do in ChoreBoy Code Studio.

## Trigger conditions

This rule applies when a change modifies any of the following:

- menu labels, menu structure, toolbar labels, button labels, dialog labels, panel labels
- project/file workflows (open, create, run, debug, stop, package, plugin management)
- settings behavior or settings defaults
- keyboard shortcuts or shortcut defaults
- run/debug/log/troubleshooting behavior shown to users
- plugin UX (install/enable/disable/safe mode/quarantine/trust prompts)
- error messages, warnings, or user guidance text
- user-facing file paths or location guidance

## Required actions

When this rule triggers, you must do all of the following in the same change:

1. Update affected chapter(s) under `docs/manual/chapters/`.
2. Update screenshot metadata in `docs/manual/screenshots/shot_list.json` if any screenshot relevance changed.
3. Replace affected screenshot files under `docs/manual/screenshots/` when UI visuals changed.
4. Update `docs/manual/feature_trace_matrix.md` if feature-to-chapter mapping changed.
5. Run:
   - `python3 docs/manual/build_manual.py --check`
   - `python3 docs/manual/build_manual.py --pdf`
6. Ensure generated PDF exists at:
   - `docs/manual/dist/ChoreBoy_Code_Studio_User_Manual_v0.1.pdf`

## Hard constraints

- Do not mark manual work as complete if the PDF was not regenerated after user-facing changes.
- Do not leave stale screenshots that contradict current UI.
- Do not document TODO or unshipped behavior as available features.

## Exception policy

Only skip manual updates if the change is strictly internal and has zero user-facing impact.
If skipped, explicitly state why this rule did not trigger in your change notes.

